    <fullPolicyText>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "markup": "<p>The company will reimburse reasonable and necessary expenses incurred while conducting authorized company business. This includes travel, lodging, meals, supplies, and other approved expenditures directly related to your role and responsibilities.</p>\n<h4>Eligibility and Scope:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Reimbursements must be pre-approved by your manager or department head.</li>\n<li>Expenses must support valid business activities and be documented with <strong>itemized receipts</strong>.</li>\n<li>All reimbursement requests must be submitted using the company’s designated expense form or system.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Submission Requirements:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Submit expense reports within <strong>30 days</strong> of incurring the expense.</li>\n<li>Include original or scanned itemized receipts for all expenses over $25.</li>\n<li>Use clear and accurate descriptions for each expense item and assign it to the correct business purpose or project.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Non-Reimbursable Expenses Include:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Alcohol (unless specifically approved for a company event)</li>\n<li>Fines or penalties (e.g., traffic tickets)</li>\n<li>Personal items or services unrelated to business needs</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We trust our employees to exercise good judgment when spending company funds. Any questionable or excessive expenses may be denied and subject to further review.</p>\n<p>If you are uncertain whether an expense is reimbursable, check with your manager or the HR team before incurring the cost. Failure to comply with these guidelines may result in a denial of reimbursement or disciplinary action.</p>",
