      "stateName": "California",
      "statePolicyText": {
        "markup": "<p><strong>California:</strong> California Labor Code Section 2802 requires employers to reimburse employees for all “necessary expenditures or losses incurred” as part of job duties. This includes mileage, personal device usage (if required), and home office expenses when remote work is mandated. Contact HR if you believe additional reimbursement is warranted.</p>\n<p><strong>Illinois:</strong> Illinois law (820 ILCS 115/9.5) also requires reimbursement for necessary work expenses. All expenses must be submitted within 30 calendar days unless otherwise agreed upon in writing. If you miss the deadline, the company may deny the reimbursement request.</p>",
